1
00:00:05,990 --> 00:00:08,140
<i>Previously on "The Magicians"...</i>

2
00:00:08,150 --> 00:00:09,480
There's too much magic.

3
00:00:09,490 --> 00:00:11,480
Everything that I touch just...

4
00:00:11,490 --> 00:00:13,079
it grows like crazy.

5
00:00:13,080 --> 00:00:14,860
I'm gonna let your bullshit slide

6
00:00:14,870 --> 00:00:16,860
on account of you so
recently being possessed

7
00:00:16,870 --> 00:00:18,900
by a homicidal monster.

8
00:00:18,910 --> 00:00:20,360
<i>There was a blood worm scare,</i>

9
00:00:20,370 --> 00:00:22,169
so the Library gave a lot
of hedges the Reed's Mark.

10
00:00:22,170 --> 00:00:24,799
<i>I found a spell to remove
the Marks in a Depository.</i>

11
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:27,340
I get you're on a mission.
One of you's got to jet.

12
00:00:27,350 --> 00:00:29,469
Either one of you can hang for eternity.

13
00:00:29,470 --> 00:00:32,010
I've earned the right to step off.

14
00:00:32,020 --> 00:00:33,930
We're here to study with Mayakovsky.

15
00:00:33,940 --> 00:00:35,809
I hate all of you.

16
00:00:35,810 --> 00:00:36,860
Professor?

17
00:00:37,720 --> 00:00:38,800
_

18
00:00:39,270 --> 00:00:41,020
"Best bitches."

19
00:00:41,030 --> 00:00:43,069
Wear this, and you'll see what I see.

20
00:00:43,070 --> 00:00:45,550
I'm Clarion, the goddess of melody.

21
00:00:45,560 --> 00:00:48,220
The way that you're imagining
the Harmonic Convergence

22
00:00:48,230 --> 00:00:49,460
isn't quite enough.

23
00:00:49,470 --> 00:00:52,539
<i>When all the spells cast by
all the Magicians go haywire,</i>

24
00:00:52,540 --> 00:00:55,579
<i>you're gonna get earthquakes,
starvation, plague.</i>

25
00:00:55,580 --> 00:00:57,629
She didn't have time to be delicate.

26
00:00:57,630 --> 00:00:59,499
You can't travel anymore.

27
00:00:59,500 --> 00:01:01,629
What exactly are we looking for, sir?

28
00:01:01,630 --> 00:01:04,080
Not what. Who.

29
00:01:04,090 --> 00:01:06,520
- You two know each other?
- No.

30
00:01:06,530 --> 00:01:08,249
Well, your subjects
are rightly grateful.

31
00:01:08,250 --> 00:01:09,350
For sending that letter?

32
00:01:09,360 --> 00:01:11,634
AKA that thing I totally
didn't do; you did.

33
00:01:11,635 --> 00:01:14,053
I was gonna let you die for Fillory.

34
00:01:14,060 --> 00:01:15,809
The Convergence can be stopped.

35
00:01:15,810 --> 00:01:19,830
All you have to do is move...

36
00:01:19,840 --> 00:01:21,070
that.

37
00:01:23,300 --> 00:01:25,490
The Harmonic Convergence.

38
00:01:25,500 --> 00:01:29,330
- AKA the end of the world.
- Not necessarily.

39
00:01:29,340 --> 00:01:31,790
This constellation forms a cosmic sigil

40
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:33,899
that increases magical intensity.

41
00:01:33,900 --> 00:01:36,489
It has happened in the past
without causing an apocalypse.

42
00:01:36,490 --> 00:01:38,239
But now there's surges of magic.

43
00:01:38,240 --> 00:01:41,489
So we get the disaster movie
Clarion was talking about.

44
00:01:41,490 --> 00:01:44,829
The Convergence will only occur
during this perfect alignment.

45
00:01:44,830 --> 00:01:47,570
If we move the moon out of position...

46
00:01:47,580 --> 00:01:49,530
No Convergence, no Circumstance,

47
00:01:49,540 --> 00:01:50,640
no apocalypse.

48
00:01:50,650 --> 00:01:54,590
The moon is not just a rock in space.
It has certain properties.

49
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:56,509
- Like?
- Magic doesn't work on it.

50
00:01:56,510 --> 00:01:58,960
Thanks to Magicians
casting haphazardly on it

51
00:01:58,970 --> 00:02:01,360
for millennia, the moon is
now covered by a crust

52
00:02:01,370 --> 00:02:03,530
of spell debris, blocking new spells.

53
00:02:03,540 --> 00:02:06,559
If we move any piece out
of place, no Convergence.

54
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:08,960
Well, what if we just moved Mars?

55
00:02:08,970 --> 00:02:11,439
She said with a straight face.

56
00:02:11,440 --> 00:02:13,819
The other pieces are planets.

57
00:02:13,820 --> 00:02:15,840
We can't move them
because they are, well,

58
00:02:15,850 --> 00:02:17,660
very big and far away.

59
00:02:17,670 --> 00:02:19,290
The moon is the only celestial body

60
00:02:19,300 --> 00:02:20,610
we stand a chance of affecting.

61
00:02:20,620 --> 00:02:22,860
But won't that screw
with the Circumstances?

62
00:02:22,870 --> 00:02:24,369
What will magic be like when we're done?

63
00:02:24,370 --> 00:02:25,820
Impossible to know.

64
00:02:25,830 --> 00:02:28,370
It will be a brand-new Circumstance.

65
00:02:29,030 --> 00:02:32,290
But to get to that problem,
we need to solve this one.

66
00:02:32,300 --> 00:02:33,990
Good, well, I hope you have some ideas,

67
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:35,209
because we're striking out.

68
00:02:35,210 --> 00:02:37,720
I do. Consult the Lunatics.

69
00:02:39,050 --> 00:02:41,429
- The lunatics?
- Short for "Lunar Fanatics."

70
00:02:41,430 --> 00:02:44,310
In the Middle Ages,
people thought insanity

71
00:02:44,320 --> 00:02:46,350
was caused by changing
phases of the moon.

72
00:02:46,360 --> 00:02:49,389
In fact, it was often a Lunatic
in the throes of worship.

73
00:02:49,390 --> 00:02:52,510
They claimed to be able to
achieve a magical connection

74
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:55,150
with the moon and even under
some circumstances...

75
00:02:55,160 --> 00:02:56,180
move it.

76
00:02:56,190 --> 00:02:57,690
Well, that sounds useful.

77
00:02:57,700 --> 00:03:00,590
- Mm.
- Well, if it's just branding,

78
00:03:00,600 --> 00:03:02,280
it means they're not
really crazy, right?

79
00:03:02,290 --> 00:03:05,370
My dad always said that
they were batshit insane,

80
00:03:05,380 --> 00:03:07,810
and he married my mom,
so he had a pretty high bar

81
00:03:07,820 --> 00:03:08,930
for mental instability.

82
00:03:08,940 --> 00:03:12,390
Regardless, they know more
about the moon than anyone.

83
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:15,870
I believe that talking to them
is our only chance at success.

84
00:03:15,880 --> 00:03:18,839
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

85
00:03:18,840 --> 00:03:21,880
<i>[EERIE MUSIC]</i>

86
00:03:21,890 --> 00:03:23,840
<i>♪ </i>

