88
00:03:33,230 --> 00:03:34,690
_

89
00:03:34,700 --> 00:03:35,979
<i>What people don't understand</i>

90
00:03:35,980 --> 00:03:37,830
is there is a skeleton of the universe,

91
00:03:37,840 --> 00:03:39,090
but we are the bones.

92
00:03:39,100 --> 00:03:41,410
Oh, that's good to know.

93
00:03:41,420 --> 00:03:42,690
I am a humerus.

94
00:03:42,700 --> 00:03:45,150
You? Patella.

95
00:03:45,160 --> 00:03:47,690
We wanted to ask you about the moon.

96
00:03:47,700 --> 00:03:49,290
Can we talk about it?

97
00:03:49,300 --> 00:03:52,290
It... it?

98
00:03:52,300 --> 00:03:54,040
Her Lunacy...

99
00:03:55,340 --> 00:03:59,110
Identifies as she/her.

100
00:03:59,120 --> 00:04:01,750
That's right. We knew that, right?

101
00:04:01,760 --> 00:04:03,780
- Of course.
- We know.

102
00:04:03,790 --> 00:04:06,679
If we wanted to move Her,
how could we do that?

103
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:09,160
You don't move Her.

104
00:04:09,170 --> 00:04:11,660
Okay, listen, Reba.

105
00:04:11,670 --> 00:04:14,599
In just a few days, a whole lot
of people are going to die.

106
00:04:14,600 --> 00:04:15,810
That's a whole lot people

107
00:04:15,820 --> 00:04:17,399
that will never get to worship the moon.

108
00:04:17,400 --> 00:04:19,970
They will never get to
know Her like you do.

109
00:04:19,980 --> 00:04:23,700
If She can help us save
all of those lives...

110
00:04:23,710 --> 00:04:26,270
imagine everyone that will realize

111
00:04:26,280 --> 00:04:28,640
just how much She deserves their love,

112
00:04:28,650 --> 00:04:29,989
their reverence.

113
00:04:29,990 --> 00:04:31,667
So will you help us?

114
00:04:33,790 --> 00:04:35,810
Just to be clear.

115
00:04:36,890 --> 00:04:39,290
You don't move Her.

116
00:04:39,300 --> 00:04:41,629
You ask Her to move.

117
00:04:41,630 --> 00:04:45,049
And She won't let you speak to
Her unless you get moon brain.

118
00:04:45,050 --> 00:04:46,929
So one of us needs moon brain.

119
00:04:46,930 --> 00:04:49,960
Not one of you. Three of you.

120
00:04:49,970 --> 00:04:52,710
A single Magician cannot
generate enough power

121
00:04:52,720 --> 00:04:53,889
to reach Her.

122
00:04:53,890 --> 00:04:55,640
So it's a cooperative spell then.

123
00:04:55,650 --> 00:04:57,769
It is a sign of respect, Kneecap,

124
00:04:57,770 --> 00:05:00,399
that allows you to see
Her as She truly is.

125
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:03,240
If you have moon brain,
then you will see Her aura.

126
00:05:03,250 --> 00:05:05,430
Now it is red, but when you
perform the Dianic Ritual,

127
00:05:05,440 --> 00:05:06,449
Her aura will change.

128
00:05:06,450 --> 00:05:08,340
If it is yellow, She is considering.

129
00:05:08,350 --> 00:05:10,690
If it is green, She is listening.

130
00:05:10,700 --> 00:05:14,720
Only then may you ask Her

131
00:05:14,730 --> 00:05:15,960
to move.

132
00:05:15,970 --> 00:05:17,250
Red, yellow, green.

133
00:05:17,260 --> 00:05:19,530
The guy who invented the stoplight,

134
00:05:19,540 --> 00:05:21,419
was he a Lunatic too?

135
00:05:21,420 --> 00:05:23,910
William Potts? Yeah.

136
00:05:23,920 --> 00:05:25,690
Oh, cool.

137
00:05:25,700 --> 00:05:28,130
All three Magicians
must perform the ritual

138
00:05:28,140 --> 00:05:30,600
until the moon is listening.

139
00:05:30,610 --> 00:05:34,170
A warning: once Her aura is green,
She may choose to listen

140
00:05:34,180 --> 00:05:36,519
to anyone who calls to Her, so be ready.

141
00:05:36,520 --> 00:05:39,019
You must choose one,
the strongest among you,

142
00:05:39,020 --> 00:05:41,860
to speak to Her, like the
old Lunatics taught us to.

143
00:05:43,110 --> 00:05:44,698
For this second part,
however, there is a price.

144
00:05:44,700 --> 00:05:48,700
- A price, like blood?
- It is like blood to Her.

145
00:05:48,710 --> 00:05:51,829
You will need a piece
of Her. A sacrifice.

146
00:05:51,830 --> 00:05:53,790
A piece?

147
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:55,999
- Or like a moon rock?
- Yes.

148
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:58,270
But be aware,

149
00:05:58,280 --> 00:06:00,300
this will destroy it,

150
00:06:00,310 --> 00:06:03,000
so don't use your favorite one.

151
00:06:04,170 --> 00:06:06,629
This is the price of
speaking to the moon.

152
00:06:06,630 --> 00:06:08,759
Just a few more questions.

153
00:06:08,760 --> 00:06:12,010
What is moon brain,
and how do we get it?

154
00:06:12,020 --> 00:06:15,099
- Everyone line up.
- Pudding time!

155
00:06:15,100 --> 00:06:17,139
Lovely to speak to you.

156
00:06:17,140 --> 00:06:19,059
You too, Kneecap. [CLICKS TONGUE]

157
00:06:19,060 --> 00:06:22,120
<i>[FUNKY MUSIC]</i>

158
00:06:22,130 --> 00:06:24,060
<i>♪ </i>

159
00:06:24,070 --> 00:06:27,560
You ever just spin a globe,
stick your finger down,

160
00:06:27,570 --> 00:06:29,730
see where it lands?

161
00:06:29,740 --> 00:06:31,070
It's almost always water,

162
00:06:31,080 --> 00:06:32,390
because, well, duh.

163
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:35,800
Earth is mostly water, but
sometimes it's the Sahara,

164
00:06:35,810 --> 00:06:38,660
sometimes the Urals.

165
00:06:38,670 --> 00:06:41,669
That's what you'd be doing
if you tried to travel.

166
00:06:41,670 --> 00:06:44,879
Only instead of the
globe, the multiverse,

167
00:06:44,880 --> 00:06:47,750
which is bigger and deadlier.

168
00:06:47,760 --> 00:06:49,250
Afraid you'd say that.

169
00:06:49,260 --> 00:06:50,890
I looked at everything I could think of,

170
00:06:50,900 --> 00:06:52,610
magical and medical.

171
00:06:52,620 --> 00:06:54,600
Nada. You're grounded.

172
00:06:55,970 --> 00:06:57,590
All right, well, since
I ain't traveling,

173
00:06:57,600 --> 00:06:58,760
I should probably step down.

174
00:06:58,770 --> 00:07:00,318
Uh, if you're offering your resignation,

175
00:07:00,320 --> 00:07:01,320
I don't accept.

176
00:07:01,330 --> 00:07:03,100
Not offering. Stating.

177
00:07:03,110 --> 00:07:05,229
With Dean Fogg out indefinitely,

178
00:07:05,230 --> 00:07:08,150
Brakebills has instituted our
Dean Vanishment Protocol.

179
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:11,000
Of course, that's a thing here.

180
00:07:11,010 --> 00:07:13,340
Yeah, and uh... [CLEARS THROAT]

181
00:07:13,350 --> 00:07:14,869
That makes me acting Dean Lipson.

182
00:07:14,870 --> 00:07:16,280
There's no instruction manual,

183
00:07:16,290 --> 00:07:17,980
so I'm kinda dean-ing on the fly here,

184
00:07:17,990 --> 00:07:19,110
but one thing I do know

185
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:21,510
is losing a professor who was disabled

186
00:07:21,520 --> 00:07:23,039
on school grounds ain't happening.

187
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:25,590
I mean, the optics would
be pure shitflakes.

188
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:29,470
So your contract will be
honored and enforced.

189
00:07:30,320 --> 00:07:32,760
Oh, also.

190
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:35,930
We need a new Welters coach.

191
00:07:38,900 --> 00:07:41,800
I've been on the inside,
and I'm telling you

192
00:07:41,810 --> 00:07:43,349
it's a goddamn goose-stepping,

193
00:07:43,350 --> 00:07:46,109
fairy-snatching, ethnic
cleansing Gestapo.

194
00:07:46,110 --> 00:07:48,310
To be fair, the ethnic
cleansing happened

195
00:07:48,320 --> 00:07:50,239
after the Dark King left, so...

196
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:52,199
He's innocent because he delegates?

197
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:53,730
No, that's not what I'm saying.

198
00:07:53,740 --> 00:07:56,110
Someone in this castle ordered
the hunt on that Fairy.

199
00:07:56,120 --> 00:07:57,450
It could have been the Dark King,

200
00:07:57,460 --> 00:07:58,850
but if it was someone else,

201
00:07:58,860 --> 00:08:00,659
killing Seb might just
make things worse.

202
00:08:00,660 --> 00:08:05,880
So we have to find out
who before we... coup.

203
00:08:07,370 --> 00:08:10,009
I just wanna stab someone.

204
00:08:10,010 --> 00:08:12,300
I haven't heard you
this bloodthirsty in...

205
00:08:12,310 --> 00:08:14,799
well, not that long,
but still, it's notable.

206
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:17,340
Maybe I'm a bit on edge.

207
00:08:17,350 --> 00:08:19,219
Josh keeps wanting to talk.

208
00:08:19,220 --> 00:08:20,410
You mean about how you wanted

209
00:08:20,420 --> 00:08:21,518
to leave him in the past to die?

210
00:08:21,520 --> 00:08:22,940
Yeah, that.

211
00:08:23,940 --> 00:08:26,150
So far, I'm doing a good
job of avoiding him,

212
00:08:26,160 --> 00:08:27,810
but eventually he's gonna sneak...

213
00:08:27,820 --> 00:08:29,020
Guys.

214
00:08:29,030 --> 00:08:31,590
- Hey, what's up?
- 'Sup?

215
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:33,028
First off, kudos on the hiding spot.

216
00:08:33,030 --> 00:08:34,239
It took me forever to find you.

217
00:08:34,240 --> 00:08:35,659
Pretty busy here, Josh.

218
00:08:35,660 --> 00:08:36,660
You're busy?

219
00:08:36,670 --> 00:08:37,869
I just got promoted to head chef.

220
00:08:37,870 --> 00:08:40,060
- Oh, congratulations.
- Thank you.

221
00:08:40,070 --> 00:08:41,990
But I'm about to bail on a state dinner

222
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:44,530
and leave it to my incompetent
sous-chef because...

223
00:08:44,540 --> 00:08:46,400
Apocalypse! Now!

224
00:08:46,410 --> 00:08:48,310
Josh, would you just give it up?

225
00:08:48,320 --> 00:08:49,999
He keeps trying to get us
to join his film club,

226
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:51,709
which I told him would
never work on a planet

227
00:08:51,710 --> 00:08:53,759
with no electricity or taste.

228
00:08:53,760 --> 00:08:57,009
Uh, no, uh, sorry.
This one's just a little shy.

229
00:08:57,010 --> 00:08:58,450
It... it's okay, buddy.

230
00:08:58,460 --> 00:09:01,970
- Help us stop the...
- Apocalypse! Now!

231
00:09:02,890 --> 00:09:05,280
- Oh.
- We need to get back to Earth.

232
00:09:05,290 --> 00:09:06,850
Margo, our talk will have to wait

233
00:09:06,860 --> 00:09:08,520
till after we save the world.

234
00:09:08,530 --> 00:09:10,730
Oh, but then I have my
nephew's bar mitzvah.

235
00:09:10,740 --> 00:09:12,360
So after that?

236
00:09:13,570 --> 00:09:15,199
- Mazel.
- Thanks.

237
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:17,300
[SIGHS]

238
00:09:17,310 --> 00:09:20,460
What about our thing? We have
a lot of fact-finding to do

239
00:09:20,470 --> 00:09:22,119
before I can get to stabbing.

240
00:09:22,120 --> 00:09:23,570
No problem.

241
00:09:23,580 --> 00:09:25,289
I know just who to handle it.

242
00:09:25,290 --> 00:09:27,039
<i>You want me to what?</i>

243
00:09:27,040 --> 00:09:30,340
Just find out who in the
castle hates Fairies.

244
00:09:30,350 --> 00:09:32,580
Okay? And what they're doing to them.

245
00:09:32,590 --> 00:09:34,299
And why Fairies in the first place?

246
00:09:34,300 --> 00:09:37,210
And maybe talk to some Fairies,
get their side of things.

247
00:09:37,220 --> 00:09:39,490
- Okay.
- And while you're at it...

248
00:09:39,500 --> 00:09:41,219
anything else that seems important.

249
00:09:41,220 --> 00:09:43,130
Okay, okay, okay.

250
00:09:43,140 --> 00:09:45,610
No, um... That seems like a
lot of open-ended questions.

251
00:09:45,620 --> 00:09:47,610
- Mm-hmm.
- I got this maid job

252
00:09:47,620 --> 00:09:48,710
to be close to you guys,

253
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:51,250
and now you're deserting me? [CHUCKLES]

254
00:09:51,260 --> 00:09:53,650
I want to stop an apocalypse too.

255
00:09:54,800 --> 00:09:56,830
Every apocalypse-stopping mission

256
00:09:56,840 --> 00:09:58,860
needs a maid on the outside.

257
00:09:58,870 --> 00:10:00,870
